=Extract a structured patient profile from these medical documents.

=== EHR DOCUMENT ===
{{ $json.ehr_text }}

=== DOCTOR TRANSCRIPT ===
{{ $json.transcript_text }}

=== OUTPUT FORMAT ===

Return a JSON object with this exact structure:

{
  "diseases": [
    {
      "name": "PRIMARY_DISEASE_ABBREVIATION",
      "nyha_class": "CLASS_IF_CHF_OR_NULL",
      "ejection_fraction": "PERCENTAGE_OR_NULL",
      "comorbidities": ["other", "conditions", "as", "lowercase"],
      "metrics": ["from_this_list_only: daily_weight, heart_rate, spo2, bp_systolic, bp_diastolic, blood_glucose, temperature"],
      "thresholds": {
        "metric_name": "concise threshold description"
      },
      "symptom_options": ["snake_case_symptoms", "relevant_to_primary_disease"],
      "mood_options": ["great", "good", "okay", "bad", "struggling"]
    }
  ],
  "medications": [
    {
      "name": "MedicationName",
      "dosage": "XXmg",
      "times": ["HH:MM", "HH:MM"]
    }
  ]
}

=== RULES ===

1. ONE disease entry only — use the PRIMARY diagnosis. List other conditions in "comorbidities".
2. Use disease abbreviation for name (e.g., "CHF" not "Congestive Heart Failure").
3. Thresholds should be concise (e.g., "gain >2kg in 2 days", "below 94%").
4. symptom_options: only symptoms relevant to the PRIMARY disease, snake_case, 5-8 options.
5. mood_options: always exactly ["great", "good", "okay", "bad", "struggling"].
6. medications: only include medications mentioned in the documents, with exact dosages and times.
7. times must be in 24h format (e.g., "08:00", "14:00", "20:00").
